&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports and demonstrates IMA’s core values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains overall responsibility of the entire renewal with the Producer (policy review, setting the game plan, loss analysis, program design, data completeness within AMS, coverage &amp;amp; premium discrepancy issues, etc.) for all existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports in winning new business and set up of new accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains intimate knowledge of clients&#39; business operations, strategies, and needs throughout the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kicks-off the client renewal process by creating the Game Plan and completing a coverage analysis (if applicable) and conducting thorough reviews of the policies and all relevant documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepares for and facilitates meetings with key IMA stakeholders and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Crafts the marketing strategies, reviews submissions, and engages in negotiations with underwriters to determine the relevant content to include in proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursues mastery of the craft through on-going education and awareness of industry trends, products, and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops &amp;amp; maintains carrier relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages a book of business with $900k - 2 Million in revenue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plays a lead role on three or more large/complex client accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7 + years Experience within the insurance industry, including at least 2 years in an Account Executive of equivalent role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in construction, real estate, and health services verticals preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think strategically based on client’s priorities and marketplace cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading and developing people&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to delegate and hold team &amp;amp; partners accountable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within Applied Epic preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with MS Office products required (specifically PowerPoint, Outlook, Word, and Excel)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel may be required when necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains increased technical knowledge both insurance industry and book of client’s industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holds at least one general insurance designation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:120,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:260}&quot;&gt;#LI-AG1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
