&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;POSITION SUMMARY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide client service assistance and support to specified producers and their commercial clients by telephone and E-mail. Provide ongoing support to clients in person including on-site visits to the client Assist with both new client presentations and renewals by performing the following duties:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DUTIES&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Duties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively and cooperatively with others, with a commitment to a workplace of dignity and respect, in compliance with equal employment opportunity standards and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accept coaching and direction from supervisors and managers, in compliance with the Agency&#39;s policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to field telephone inquiries from clients about their current coverage and insurance contracts as well as general questions about insurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the resolution of claims issues with carriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing, in-person consulting with assigned clients to maximize our retention of accounts. This may entail coordinating service issues with the account service manager assigned to the account and, if needed, assisting personally with the resolution of complex service and billing issues Follow established departmental and agency processes and procedures, tracking activities, client history, and communication with client and documenting them in agency system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When requested, monitor specified producer email inbox so general and time-sensitive client service requests can be handled while they are out of the office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist CSMs with technical coverage and contract reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Renewal Clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with producer to determine client&#39;s needs at renewal and then coordinate the data collection and proposal preparation of appropriate proposals from insurance carriers to meet those needs within a specified timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with producers on renewals and coordinate internal functions so that the producer receives all necessary renewal information and proposals on a timely basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Renewal Timeline process, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist producer and often times lead the marketing effort of commercial accounts to the carriers at renewal including gathering of the necessary data from the client, analysis of carrier proposals for suitability to the client&#39;s needs and negotiation of final rates and coverage with carriers and other vendors as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with marketing team or Client Service Manager to prepare renewal for submission to marketplace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up marketing team/CSM and/or carriers to make sure that proposals are received on timely basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with marketing team/CSM to review for accuracy the quotes and proposal to client.&amp;nbsp; Where necessary, compare and illustrate coverage options for internal or external presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the preparation of renewal presentation package with internal staff and assist producer with the presentations of the renewal to major clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate client renewals and provide other services as required so that producer can maximize time for new business production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New Business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide analysis assistance to producer for new prospects related to W3 Advantage Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the producer and often times lead the marketing effort of commercial accounts to carriers, including gathering of the necessary data from the client, analysis of carrier

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;POSITION SUMMARY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;: The Employee Benefits Client Executive is responsible for delivering high-quality and efficient service to both internal and external clients through day-to-day account management of an assigned group of accounts. Builds and solidifies relationships with existing clients by providing exceptional ongoing service. In partnership with the Production Team, takes a leadership role in the renewal process, ensuring that the best possible solution is delivered to the client in a high-quality &amp;amp; timely manner:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DUTIES&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Planning and Consultation&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead both long-term and short-term strategic consultation and planning efforts for client benefit programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure programs and plan design are aligned with all applicable regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize intermediate knowledge of underwriting practices to analyze claims data and provide applied explanations to the client and internal team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Renewal and Coverage Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and direct the renewal process for all lines of coverage, including negotiating rate renewals and recommending carrier changes or alternative funding arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and oversee the service teams&#39; work assignments related to project management, claims escalation and resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with a Client Service Associate to verify the accuracy of presentation spreadsheets by comparing carrier proposals and assist in assembling formal proposals for clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship Development and Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strong carrier and vendor relationships to support and lead negotiation and advocacy during client coverage placement and renewal process, utilizing department peers and/or leadership as necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with internal subject matter experts and leadership to identify current and emerging markets and products, delivering solutions aligned with clients&#39; goals through ongoing commitment to ongoing learning and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Communication and Education&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver client communications, including presentations at client meetings, to inform and educate on benefits legislation, compliance, industry trends, and new products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field telephone inquiries as needed from both clients and their employees about their current coverage and insurance contracts, as well as general questions about insurance or benefits and regulations pertaining to insurance and benefits such as COBRA, HIPAA, and S125.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make routine service calls to the client&#39;s workplace as needed within their team structure to address service issues and proactively demonstrate our high level of commitment to superior service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting and Enrollment Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete annual Stewardship Reports and quarterly Claims Utilization Reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technological support and conduct annual open enrollment meetings, including employee presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan annual client enrollments, including the development of enrollment strategies and educational materials to help employees understand and effectively utilize their benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Management and Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;IMA is seeking an Account Executive to join our growing National Real Estate Team! This person is responsible for maintaining the overall responsibility of the entire renewal policy review, setting plans, conducting loss analysis, program design, data completeness, and coverage and premium discrepancy issues for all existing accounts. This role is eligible for remote work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities for this role include, but are not limited to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in winning new business and set up of new accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain intimate knowledge of clients&#39; business operations, strategies, and needs throughout the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kicks-off the client renewal process by creating the Game Plan and completing a coverage analysis (if applicable) and conducting thorough review of the policy and all relevant documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare for and facilitate meetings with key IMA stakeholders and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft the marketing strategies, review submissions, and engage in negotiations with underwriters to determine the relevant content to include in proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursue mastery of the craft through on-going education and awareness of industry trends, products, and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain carrier relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a book of business greater than $1.3 million in revenue&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% + book of business focused on large/complex accounts. Play a lead role with large/complex accounts, based on primary industry levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10% + of time is spent supporting producers in winning new business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify with client’s priorities then create a vision for their insurance program with alignment to their risk management goals, and understand client’s business philosophy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure a strong, long-term partnership with assigned clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer client and internal team management and coaching as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with internal ancillary teams to ensure client and company success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and demonstrate IMA’s core values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Value and understand the importance of diversity, equity, and inclusion among all IMA associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required skills and experiences:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in insurance or related industry based on the assigned book of business required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think strategically based on client’s priorities and marketplace cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to delegate and hold team and partners accountable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within Applied Epic preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with MS Office products required (specifically PowerPoint, Outlook, Word, and Excel)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel up 20-25% of the time, depending on the location of the role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at understanding the client’s entire business as it relates to insurance protection (matching to their aversion level of risk) as it relates to specific terms &amp;amp; conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthens IMA brand as subject matter expert (speaking at conferences, white papers, carrier relationships, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attain and maintain professional designation or license – Property &amp;amp; Casualty insurance license, within the first 30-90 days of hire&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holds formal specialty designation preferred (ARM, CPCU, Industry specific designation, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:120,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:260}&quot;&gt;#LI-AG1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Have to Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Richards Group an IMA Company is looking for a highly motivated Account Manager to join our Personal Lines team. If you have strong interpersonal skills, a passion for building relationships, and a commitment to exceptional service, we’d love to hear from you! This position offers flexibility with the option to work remotely. Because we value in-person collaboration for training, team building, and strategic meetings, qualified candidates must live within reasonable traveling distance to one of our VT or NH locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior industry exposure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An active Property &amp;amp; Casualty License&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong sense of integrity, professionalism, and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team-oriented mindset and high level of self-motivation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for delivering outstanding customer service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with computer systems and efficient, accurate data entry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using AMS 360 or a similar agency management system preferred not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Richards Group has joined IMA’s national platform, giving our teams access to expanded resources, new career pathways, enhanced strength, and employee ownership opportunities, all while preserving the local leadership and deep community roots that define who we are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-TC1&lt;/p&gt;
