&lt;p&gt;The Client Service Representative serves as the primary operational and service interface for clients focused on delivering responsive support, supporting Private Wealth advisors, and ensuring a consistent client experience.&amp;nbsp; We provide service to our clients with passion and integrity. At IMA, we have a strong focus on employee development and collaboration. Through comprehensive training, mentorship, and client-centric innovation, our service professionals are empowered to transform clients’ lives while growing in their own careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage existing client relationships with moderate guidance by processing client requests, resolving client inquiries, and making sure key client information is up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate Proactive solutions-based approach to enhancing client relations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onboard new clients by collecting client data, financial statements, and training on digital tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive client retention by proactively reaching out to clients and documenting follow up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with an investment team, compliance, financial planning and Private Wealth advisors to provide a consistent client experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with partners to ensure consistent client service quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform administrative duties that support the Private Wealth advisor including but not limited to answering phones, scheduling appointments, and business travel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in available training and educational opportunities to stay current on policies and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports and demonstrates IMA’s core values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Values and understands the importance of diversity, equity, and inclusion among all IMA associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other work-related duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 to 3 years of similar or related experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must currently hold, or obtain within 120 days of employment, a FINRA Series 65 license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continued employment is contingent upon obtaining the license within this timeframe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with high-net-worth individuals and families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Salesforce, Microsoft Office suite, and AI tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
